OL,6,FIn 1898, an American psychiatry
OL,7,Fprofessor named Daniel Brower came up
OL,8,Fwith an odd idea he called
OL,9,F"auto-intoxication". In a paper he sent
OL,10,Fto the Journal of the American Medical
OL,11,FAssociation, he suggested that an
OL,12,Fexcess of bacteria in the gut could,
OL,13,Fvia the production of bacterial waste
OL,14,Fproducts, cause "melancholia" ` what we
OL,15,Fnow know as depression. The body was
OL,16,Fliterally toxifying itself, producing
OL,17,Fchemicals in its own gut that had
OL,18,Framifications for organs far beyond the
OL,19,Fintestine.
OL,3,CDoes gut bacteria really cause
OL,4,Cdepression? Here's what science says
